{
  "id": "56539956-083b-49a4-bdb3-b02705e6b6e4",
  "name": "research-mode",
  "description": "Deep web research mode. Takes a research question, autonomously searches the web in iterative cycles (decompose \u2192 search \u2192 read \u2192 extract \u2192 gap analysis \u2192 repeat), then synthesizes a comprehensive cited report. Replicates Claude's research mode behavior.\n\nUsage: /research-mode \"your research question here\"\n\nOutput: Report saved to /tmp/fc-research/report.md",
  "flowchart": {
    "blocks": {
      "1f7d8aae-2d0e-42bb-8c88-3669074c783d": {
        "id": "1f7d8aae-2d0e-42bb-8c88-3669074c783d",
        "type": "start",
        "name": "START",
        "position": {
          "x": 150,
          "y": 50
        }
      },
      "7f5ad181-70b7-4d48-90cb-7b29914e7af1": {
        "id": "7f5ad181-70b7-4d48-90cb-7b29914e7af1",
        "type": "bash",
        "name": "SETUP WORKSPACE",
        "position": {
          "x": 150,
          "y": 150
        },
        "command": "mkdir -p /tmp/fc-research && echo '# Research Knowledge Base' > /tmp/fc-research/knowledge.md && echo '[]' > /tmp/fc-research/sources.json && echo '' > /tmp/fc-research/next_queries.txt && echo 'Workspace ready'",
        "capture_output": true,
        "output_variable": "",
        "output_type": "string",
        "working_directory": "",
        "continue_on_error": false,
        "exit_code_variable": "",
        "disable_auto_git": true,
        "git_tag": null
      },
      "c23532df-eff7-4592-b43f-98f5c4a5618f": {
        "id": "c23532df-eff7-4592-b43f-98f5c4a5618f",
        "type": "prompt",
        "name": "DECOMPOSE QUERY",
        "position": {
          "x": 150,
          "y": 270
        },
        "prompt": "You are a research planner. Your job is to analyze a research question and create a thorough plan.\n\nRESEARCH QUESTION: $1\n\nTasks:\n1. Break the question into 3-7 sub-questions that together would comprehensively answer the main question\n2. For each sub-question, generate 1-2 search queries that would find relevant information\n3. Write a concise research plan summarizing what you need to find\n\nWrite your research plan to /tmp/fc-research/plan.md\nWrite the initial search queries (one per line) to /tmp/fc-research/next_queries.txt\n\nThen return the structured output below.",
        "output_schema": {
          "type": "object",
          "properties": {
            "num_sub_questions": {
              "type": "integer"
            },
            "plan_summary": {
              "type": "string"
            }
          },
          "required": [
            "num_sub_questions",
            "plan_summary"
          ]
        },
        "sound_effect": null,
        "disable_auto_git": true,
        "git_tag": null
      },
      "33d2e454-ae1a-4057-808f-76354b165189": {
        "id": "33d2e454-ae1a-4057-808f-76354b165189",
        "type": "variable",
        "name": "SET iteration=0",
        "position": {
          "x": 150,
          "y": 400
        },
        "variable_name": "iteration",
        "variable_value": "0",
        "variable_type": "int"
      },
      "d6cd1512-c422-4b72-bdaf-b48455204805": {
        "id": "d6cd1512-c422-4b72-bdaf-b48455204805",
        "type": "variable",
        "name": "SET continue=true",
        "position": {
          "x": 150,
          "y": 490
        },
        "variable_name": "should_continue",
        "variable_value": "true",
        "variable_type": "boolean"
      },
      "3605c52a-369e-4d1c-91ae-4ecf46dda2e0": {
        "id": "3605c52a-369e-4d1c-91ae-4ecf46dda2e0",
        "type": "branch",
        "name": "CONTINUE?",
        "position": {
          "x": 150,
          "y": 590
        },
        "condition": "should_continue"
      },
      "9ed42ce1-2a80-4b74-94f9-31a12bb1f943": {
        "id": "9ed42ce1-2a80-4b74-94f9-31a12bb1f943",
        "type": "branch",
        "name": "UNDER LIMIT?",
        "position": {
          "x": 150,
          "y": 690
        },
        "condition": "iteration < 15"
      },
      "95f4f55d-2cd9-477b-afd7-ece332e3e3fe": {
        "id": "95f4f55d-2cd9-477b-afd7-ece332e3e3fe",
        "type": "refresh",
        "name": "REFRESH",
        "position": {
          "x": 150,
          "y": 790
        }
      },
      "7b06767a-49f7-449b-ad27-acfb320ebbc7": {
        "id": "7b06767a-49f7-449b-ad27-acfb320ebbc7",
        "type": "prompt",
        "name": "SEARCH & ANALYZE",
        "position": {
          "x": 150,
          "y": 890
        },
        "prompt": "You are a research assistant conducting one iteration of a deep web research process.\n\nORIGINAL RESEARCH QUESTION: $1\n\nFirst, read these files to understand the current state of the research:\n1. /tmp/fc-research/plan.md \u2014 the research plan with sub-questions\n2. /tmp/fc-research/knowledge.md \u2014 all findings accumulated so far\n3. /tmp/fc-research/next_queries.txt \u2014 the search queries to use this iteration\n4. /tmp/fc-research/sources.json \u2014 sources found so far\n\nThen perform these steps:\n1. SEARCH: Use the web search tool to search for each query in next_queries.txt. Examine the results carefully.\n2. READ: Pick the 2-4 most promising results based on domain authority (.gov, .edu, major publications), relevance to unanswered sub-questions, and recency. Fetch and read the full content of those pages.\n3. EXTRACT: For each page, extract facts relevant to the research question. Note the URL and key claims.\n4. EVALUATE: Assess source credibility. Flag any contradictions with existing knowledge.\n5. GAP ANALYSIS: Compare what you now know against the research plan. What sub-questions are still unanswered? What needs more evidence?\n6. DECIDE: Based on your gap analysis:\n   - If significant gaps remain and new searches would help \u2192 should_continue = true, and write new targeted search queries to /tmp/fc-research/next_queries.txt\n   - If all sub-questions are well-answered with multiple corroborating sources \u2192 should_continue = false\n\nIMPORTANT: Append your new findings to /tmp/fc-research/knowledge.md (do NOT overwrite \u2014 append with a clear iteration header).\nUpdate /tmp/fc-research/sources.json by reading the current array and appending new source entries.\n\nThen return the structured output.",
        "output_schema": {
          "type": "object",
          "properties": {
            "should_continue": {
              "type": "boolean"
            },
            "sources_found_this_iteration": {
              "type": "integer"
            },
            "gaps_remaining": {
              "type": "string"
            },
            "iteration_summary": {
              "type": "string"
            }
          },
          "required": [
            "should_continue",
            "sources_found_this_iteration",
            "gaps_remaining",
            "iteration_summary"
          ]
        },
        "sound_effect": null,
        "disable_auto_git": true,
        "git_tag": null
      },
      "73a9b6da-6765-4d33-aa0a-7c91cb440fcf": {
        "id": "73a9b6da-6765-4d33-aa0a-7c91cb440fcf",
        "type": "bash",
        "name": "LOG ITERATION",
        "position": {
          "x": 150,
          "y": 1040
        },
        "command": "echo \"Iteration {{iteration}} complete: {{iteration_summary}}\" && echo \"Gaps remaining: {{gaps_remaining}}\"",
        "capture_output": true,
        "output_variable": "",
        "output_type": "string",
        "working_directory": "",
        "continue_on_error": true,
        "exit_code_variable": "",
        "disable_auto_git": true,
        "git_tag": null
      },
      "e2a28a93-905c-4042-bce8-dab0fd809f89": {
        "id": "e2a28a93-905c-4042-bce8-dab0fd809f89",
        "type": "bash",
        "name": "iter++",
        "position": {
          "x": 150,
          "y": 1140
        },
        "command": "echo $(({{iteration}}+1))",
        "capture_output": true,
        "output_variable": "iteration",
        "output_type": "int",
        "working_directory": "",
        "continue_on_error": false,
        "exit_code_variable": "",
        "disable_auto_git": true,
        "git_tag": null
      },
      "4249b040-10c5-4288-874c-9513fab7e0c8": {
        "id": "4249b040-10c5-4288-874c-9513fab7e0c8",
        "type": "refresh",
        "name": "REFRESH",
        "position": {
          "x": 470,
          "y": 590
        }
      },
      "9513f309-0477-400e-a55a-299d49cb8794": {
        "id": "9513f309-0477-400e-a55a-299d49cb8794",
        "type": "prompt",
        "name": "SYNTHESIZE REPORT",
        "position": {
          "x": 470,
          "y": 700
        },
        "prompt": "You are a research synthesizer. Your job is to produce a comprehensive, well-cited research report.\n\nORIGINAL RESEARCH QUESTION: $1\n\nRead these files containing all the research gathered:\n1. /tmp/fc-research/plan.md \u2014 the original research plan\n2. /tmp/fc-research/knowledge.md \u2014 ALL accumulated findings from every search iteration\n3. /tmp/fc-research/sources.json \u2014 all sources with URLs, titles, and key facts\n\nNow write a comprehensive research report following these guidelines:\n- ORGANIZE by theme or sub-question, NOT by source or iteration\n- CROSS-REFERENCE facts across multiple sources, noting where they agree or disagree\n- Use INLINE CITATIONS like [1], [2] etc. linked to the sources list\n- Include a SUMMARY section at the top (3-5 key takeaways)\n- Include a SOURCES section at the end with numbered references and URLs\n- Note any CAVEATS about source reliability or gaps in the research\n- Target 2000-4000 words \u2014 be comprehensive but avoid repetition\n\nWrite the complete report to /tmp/fc-research/report.md\n\nThen return the structured output.",
        "output_schema": {
          "type": "object",
          "properties": {
            "report_word_count": {
              "type": "integer"
            },
            "num_sources_cited": {
              "type": "integer"
            },
            "confidence_level": {
              "type": "string"
            }
          },
          "required": [
            "report_word_count",
            "num_sources_cited",
            "confidence_level"
          ]
        },
        "sound_effect": null,
        "disable_auto_git": true,
        "git_tag": null
      },
      "3cb9a286-5685-47fe-90f8-6f406f33dd45": {
        "id": "3cb9a286-5685-47fe-90f8-6f406f33dd45",
        "type": "bash",
        "name": "PRINT REPORT",
        "position": {
          "x": 470,
          "y": 850
        },
        "command": "echo '=== RESEARCH COMPLETE ===' && echo 'Report: /tmp/fc-research/report.md' && echo 'Sources: {{num_sources_cited}} cited' && echo 'Confidence: {{confidence_level}}' && echo 'Word count: ~{{report_word_count}}'",
        "capture_output": true,
        "output_variable": "",
        "output_type": "string",
        "working_directory": "",
        "continue_on_error": true,
        "exit_code_variable": "",
        "disable_auto_git": true,
        "git_tag": null
      },
      "432dc33b-53d4-4f57-a36f-99150155170c": {
        "id": "432dc33b-53d4-4f57-a36f-99150155170c",
